# Firm Output Templates

> Remove the `.example` extension to activate. These settings override
> the default output formatting in report-generating skills.

## Investment Memo Sections

Customize the section order and names for your IC process. Add or
remove sections as needed. Sections not listed here will use defaults.

1. Executive Summary
2. Company Overview
3. Market Opportunity
4. Competitive Landscape
5. Product & Technology
6. Team Assessment
7. Business Model & Unit Economics
8. Financial Analysis
9. Deal Terms & Valuation
10. Key Risks & Mitigants
11. Due Diligence Findings
12. Investment Recommendation

## Required IC Fields

Every memo must include these fields for IC review:

- Proposed check size
- Ownership target
- Expected holding period
- Key milestones for next 12 months
- Board seat / observer rights

## KPI Report Format

### Required Metrics (always show)

- ARR / MRR
- Burn rate and runway
- Customer count and growth
- Churn rate (logo and revenue)

### Optional Metrics (show if available)

- NPS score
- Employee headcount
- Pipeline value

## Portfolio Report Format

### Summary Section

- Fund size and vintage year
- Capital deployed vs committed
- Number of active investments
- MOIC, IRR, DPI at fund level

### Company Detail

- One row per company
- Columns: name, stage, invested, current value, MOIC, status
